overview:
ServiceFinder is an online marketplace for services â€“ where consumer and service providers can take advantage of the great matchmaking abilities of the Internet. The business model rests on the sale of leads to prescreened affiliated service providing companies.

After completing an online request form, with details of the desired project, the customer will then receive quotes from different companies matching that specific customer and requests.

ServiceFinder uses a well-tried search method combining refined algorithms with real-time manual searches to match the customers needs, before connecting them with prescreened service professionals. A customer-rating system helps to assure quality among the service providing companies.

Each year ServiceFinder helps over 70 000 customers receive relevant quotes from well recommended and professional service providers. This online service is completely free of charge and works for all sorts of services, whether they are domestic, business related or perhaps for a co-op association.

ServiceFinder was founded in 2006 by Jeffrey Singh, Vishal Nanda and Aleksandar Goga. Ever since then the company has continuously expanded and is now market leading in online service matching. Everyone on ServiceFinder have their minds set on making ServiceFinder top-of-mind for consumer and service providers, not just in Sweden, but internationally.

In 2011 ServiceFinder became a subsidiary of Schibsted Media Group.
